House of Representatives Member representing Sumaila/Takai Federal constituency of Kano state, Hon. Shamsudeen Dambazau has joined well-meaning leaders to felicitate with the populace as the Nation marks its 60th independence anniversary. Hon. Dambazau further used the occasion to reassure Nigerians that the current House of Representatives under Speaker Femi Gbajabiamila were committed to purposeful and people-driven governance. While also calling for support for President Muhammdu Buhari-led administration, Dambazau in a statement on Thursday, insisted that the country is better off than it was in its yesteryears. He also said that working with Governor Umar Ganduje’s government, who is our leader in Kano state, we are poised to delivering on the dividends of democracy. ” On this auspicious occasion, our fore bears had dreams of a prosperous Nigeria, making their contributions and looked up to the new generation to consolidate on their achievements. “No doubt, our journey has come with it successes, missed opportunities, challenges among others. As a people, We have and will continue to weather many storms as we continue on the path of growth and sustainable development. “Critical sectors like education, health and agriculture are getting his full attention. Government at both federal and state level has been working with critical stakeholders and security agencies to bring the insecurity situation under control” “Let me assure that i will continue to initiate and sponsor bills that would help empower our people and reposition the area economically. I will not rest until our good is better as we strive for the best. “As we celebrate Nigeria’s 60th Independence Anniversary, I urge our people at all levels to remain resolute to the ideals of one indivisible Nigeria, peace, progress and prosperity of all. ” The current challenges and difficulties will give way to a better Nigeria. God bless us” Hon. Dambazau said